# ACloudViewer Plugin Development Rules

## Plugin Architecture

- Plugins live under `plugins/core/Standard/` (standard) or `plugins/core/IO/` (I/O filters)
- Each plugin needs: `CMakeLists.txt`, `info.json`, a `.qrc` resource file
- Use `AddPlugin(NAME ...)` from `plugins/cmake/Plugins.cmake`
- Plugins link: `CVCoreLib`, `CVPluginAPI`, `CVPluginStub`

## Key Interfaces

- `ccStdPluginInterface` — base class for standard plugins
- `ecvMainAppInterface` — access to app (DB, views, console, selection)
- `ccCommandLineInterface` — register CLI commands via `registerCommand()`
- `ecvDisplayTools` — static display operations (redraw, view matrix, etc.)

## Common Patterns

- Get app interface: `m_app` (set via `setMainAppInterface()`)
- Access DB root: `m_app->dbRootObject()`
- Cast entities: `ccHObjectCaster::ToPointCloud(obj)`, `ccHObjectCaster::ToMesh(obj)`
- Force redraw: `ecvDisplayTools::RedrawDisplay()`
- View orientations: `CC_TOP_VIEW`, `CC_FRONT_VIEW`, `CC_ISO_VIEW_1`, etc.

## Build

```bash
cmake -DPLUGIN_STANDARD_QJSONRPC=ON -DPLUGIN_STANDARD_QSIBR=ON ..
make -j$(nproc)
```

## Entity Types

| Enum | Type |
|------|------|
| `CV_TYPES::POINT_CLOUD` | Point cloud |
| `CV_TYPES::MESH` | Triangle mesh |
| `CV_TYPES::POLY_LINE` | Polyline |
| `CV_TYPES::HIERARCHY_OBJECT` | Group/container |
